		   <tr><td valign="top" id="fs8" class="mform" ><span id="notbold">By:</span> <span id=>Anonymous</span></a><b><span id=></span></b>
		   <br><nobr><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Default [2.00]</nobr><br><br /><a href="/cgi-bin/pm.pl?action=addtolist&addname=Anonymous&type=Address" id="fs8"><img src="/shared/plus.gif" border="0" align="middle" height="9" width="9" alt="Add to address book"> Add to address book</a><br /><img src="/shared/transp.gif" width="135" border="0" height="1"></td><td valign="top" class="mform" width="100%"><p>Depends on which twohander you have and what weapons you have for dual wielding.<br>At the 50 plus range of levels, there are several very nice twohanded weapons.&nbsp;&nbsp;You can do more damage with a twohander in my opinion, but there will be some engagements which you may miss alot.  So the highs are higher with a good twohander, and the lows are lower.  <br>Dual wielding can result in a better average damage output, and tends to be better over time.  The down fall is you need two good 1handers, and you also have higher chances of big reposites from high level monsters.  Also critical are tend to be lower in value.<br>Overall, in most instances I distiguish using a twohander or dual wield based on a few criteria.<br>Do I need to taunt alot?  Winner dual wielding (especially if a weapon procs.)<br>Do I want to do more damage?  Winner Twohander<br>Soloing or small grouping.  Winner Dual Weild<br>Dualing.  Dual wield against casters and Rogues.  Others can use twohander.<br>My opinion, just got to look at what you trying to do.<br>54th Champion</p></td></td></tr><tr><td colspan="2" class="mform"><table border=0 cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0 width="100%"><tr><td id=fs8></td><td align=right id=fs8 >0 Replies</td></tr></table></td></tr></table><tr><td class=mhback align=right><span class=mh id=fs8><a class=mh href=/db/classes.html?class=1><img src=/shared/root_thread_ico.gif border=0 alt="Up" width=17 height=11> Thread Index</a> |  <a class=mh href=/db/classes.html?class=1&post=1><img src=/shared/new_thread_ico.gif border=0 alt="New" width=17 height=11> New Subj